gomodel:SYNGO_1626  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig1A: Gdi1 KO mice showed progressive reduction in the number of SVs in synaptic terminals with increasing age, reaching 50% reduction at P90 as compared to WT mice\nTable1(P10 and P23) & Fig2: The number of docked SVs was not significantly different between in Gdi KO versus WT mice at P90. However, the size of the reserve pool in Gdi KO mice was reduced by almost 5-fold.\nFig5A-B: Schaffer collateral pathway was stimulated with a train of 300 stimuli delivered at a frequency of 10 Hz. The progressive change in fEPSP slope ratio during the train and the subsequent recovery from depression, obtained by returning the stimulation frequency to 0.1 Hz, was compared in WT and mutant slices. In WT mice, the PTP phase lasted for 2 min and was slowly and progressively replaced by a moderate depression phase lasting 11 min and reaching a depression plateau of 85.6 ± 6.7% while PTP lasted <30 s in Gdi1 KO mice, and was soon replaced by a phase of intense depression that reached a plateau level of 71.3 ± 12%.\nFig 5C: A monoexponential fit of the first 3 min of the recovery phase revealed a faster decay of the PTP phase in KO slices.\nThe authors claim that this effect could be the consequence of the strong SV depletion observed in the KO synapses by EM, which alters the SV recruitment from the releasable pool.. Experimental description: Gdi1 heterozygote females in a pure C57Bl6/N genetic background were crossed with C57Bl6/N male mice to obtain Gdi1 mutant and WT male mice littermates" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1626" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

